# macOS build and test

On macOS, any change to C++ source, headers, or CMake **must** be validated by building and running tests.

## Required

- **Preferred (if present):** `scripts/build_tests_macos.sh` — single entrypoint, same pattern as USN_Windows.
- **Otherwise:** CMake configure, build, and `ctest` (or the test command documented in this repository’s README / AGENTS.md).
- **Scope:** When changing `*.cpp`, `*.c`, `*.h`, `*.hpp`, `*.cxx`, `*.cc`, `CMakeLists.txt`, or scripts that affect builds/tests.
- **Exception:** Pure documentation-only changes (e.g. `*.md` or comment-only) may skip this step.

## When a macOS build script exists

If `scripts/build_tests_macos.sh` exists, treat it as the **only** allowed build/test entrypoint on macOS (do not bypass it with ad-hoc `cmake`/`make` unless AGENTS.md explicitly allows an exception for a task).

## Agent note

When modifying code under macOS, **state in your response** which validation command you ran and whether it passed.

**Reference:** AGENTS.md — Build and tests.
